    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-07T17:01:10+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-07T17:01:10+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T07:31:10Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T07:31:10Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high-pressure system south of the state will move east on Wednesday allowing an upper trough to bring instability to southern parts of the state during the day, persisting into Thursday. The upper trough will precede a strong cold front that is forecast to move over South Australia later Thursday. A cooler southwest to southerly flow will gradually moderate as a stronger high-pressure system moves in from the west from Friday to be south of the state on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW009" description="Flinders" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-07T16:58:29+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T07:28:29Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Hawker, slight chance elsewhere. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h becoming light in the evening.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers south of Hawker, slight chance elsewhere. Winds northeast to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h tending north to northwesterly 15 to 25 km/h in the morning. Overnight temperatures falling to between 13 and 19 with daytime temperatures reaching around 30.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">No Rating</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:20am to 3:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers south of Hawker, slight chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm south of Hawker in the afternoon and evening. Winds north to northwesterly 25 to 35 km/h turning westerly in the late morning and early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 16 and 22 with daytime temperatures reaching 27 to 34.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower near the coast, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds southwesterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 11 and 16 with daytime temperatures reaching between 18 and 24.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower south of Hawker in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h turning southerly 20 to 30 km/h during the day. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
